  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 11.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "Now, you-- you wanted to ask me about the warriors.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "I have to start with 1938. 1938, the Hebrew equivalent is [HEBREW].",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And 5,298, that was the year equivalent to-- to 1938.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "In Hebrew [HEBREW] spelled tirzah.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And tirzah in Hebrew translates murder.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "And that's when the murders started. 1938 was the Kristallnacht.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "In November '38, that was when the first murder started, murdering the Jews.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "And sometimes in June, July of 1938, the Munich-- infamous Munich Pact or dictate where Hitler dictated to the-- to the Allies, Chamberlain and-- and-- and Daladier, I think, was the name of the French prime minister that they-- they agreed to dismantle Czechoslovakia to give back the Sudeten area to Germany.",
      "word_count": 52
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "From that time till March 15, 1939, there was a six-month window of opportunity maybe to get out.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "Because when-- when the English and the French dictated for the Czech government to surrender part of-- of the Sudeten gebeit, Sudetenland, and part of-- part of it to-- to see part of it to-- to Hungary, we were still under Czech control.",
      "word_count": 43
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "About from-- from October to March 15, on March 15, 1939, the-- the Germans moved in to Prague, occupied Czechoslovakia completely.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "The Slovaks declared [? in ?] their independence.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "The Ruthenians, in our area, declared also independence, their own independence, which was very, very scary for us.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "But it lasted only about 48 hours.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "And it collapsed when Hungary, according to the Encyclopedia Britannica, it is-- that-- that-- it was [? where ?] the acquiescence of Hitler to move into Carpathia, but I don't think that this is quite correct.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "I think they did it on their own.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "Because Hitler Germany supported the Carpathian independence.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "And they declared their independence, and-- and they declared Khust as their capital city.",
      "word_count": 14
    }
  ],
